    "Thus the super-transformer's weights W Sup are of the same size as the teacher weights W Tch).",
    "To fine-tune the super-transformer weights W Sup, in each of the subsequent stages, we freeze W Tch and propose learning two stage-specific low-rank matrices A s, B s, of the same rank, r, as A 0, B 0, that are shared across all sub-transformer models in that stage.",
    "To be precise, we impose the following structure on the weights of the sub-transformers at stage-s:W Sup:= W Tch + 2 s=1 A s * B s, W Φ = Π Φ (W Sup), ∀Φ ∈ A.",
    "(7)Stage-s of the fine-tuning process involves learning only the low-rank matrices, A s, B s, by minimizing the super-transform loss as in (3).",
